// fragment_about The POST (Quality of Public Open Space Tool) is a well-established and validated tool designed for auditing public open spaces such as parks and other greenspaces, with particular emphasis on the physical attributes that may either encourage or discourage their use for physical activity. The POST relies on direct observation and it is composed of 49 items covering four key domains: activities, environmental quality, comfort, and safety. \n\n This App was developed by Instituto de Saúde Publica da Universidade do Porto (ISPUP) and by the Centre for the Built Environment and Health of the University of Western Australia based on the original paper version of POST. \n\n Besides the user-friendly interface, this electronic version now includes other functionalities, namely storing data, mapping features, and exporting the database with the audit results.
// fragment_help Click to see POST manual Before beginning the audit, read the Quality of Public Open Space Tool (POST) manual, it is available below. When you open the App you can choose between "Start New Project" (to create a new project), "List Projects" (to re-visit previous projects), "Export Data" (to export your results and maps) or "Settings" (to configure some application attributes). \n\n When using this application for the first time, select "Start New Project". Add a name and description to the project and draw on the map a polygon corresponding to the geographic extend of the project. Then, simply add the Public Open Space that will be audited in your project, and fill up the answers to the items found in the menu tabs "Location", "General", "Activities", "Environmental Quality", "Amenities" and “Safety”. Your project can be saved at any time. After saving it, the database with the audit results can be exported to your e-mail account in .csv and .kmz format.
